snippet: With Toronto and Baltimore stronger this season, the American League East, a division that for the last 12 years has been won by a team with 95 or more victories, could have a champion with only 90 wins.
abstract: Tyler Kepner On Baseball column holds that with Toronto Blue Jays and Baltimore Orioles stronger this season, American League East, division that for 12 years has been won by team with 95 or more victories, could have champion with only 90 wins.
lead_paragraph: With Toronto and Baltimore stronger this season, the American League East, a division that for the last 12 years has been won by a team with 95 or more victories, could have a champion with only 90 wins.

headline.seo: In A.L. East, 90 Wins May Be Enough
headline.main: Early Signs of Parity in A.L. East, Where 90 Wins May Be Enough
headline.print_headline: Early Signs of Parity in A.L. East, Where 90 Wins May Be Enough
